trans-unit.source: A class that represents the results of a match operation on a <xref href="System.UriTemplate"></xref> instance.
The <xref:System.UriTemplateMatch> class represents the results of calling the <xref:System.UriTemplate.Match%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Uri%29> method.
This class is not thread safe.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.UriTemplateMatch"></xref> class.

Usually you do not directly instantiate this class, a <xref:System.UriTemplateMatch> instance is returned from the <xref:System.UriTemplate.Match%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Uri%29> or <xref:System.UriTemplateTable.MatchSingle%28System.Uri%29> method.
The <xref:System.UriTemplateTable.Match%2A> method returns a collection of <xref:System.UriTemplateMatch> as well.
Gets and sets the base URI for the template match.
A <xref href="System.Uri"></xref> instance that represents the base URI for the template match.
Gets the `BoundVariables` collection for the template match.
Each template variable name appears as a name in this collection, and the value bound to that variable is stored under the corresponding name.
The values in this collection have had all escape sequences translated into actual characters.
This name value collection uses a case insensitive search when matching variable names.
A <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.NameValueCollection"></xref> instance that contains template variable values extracted from the URI during the match.
Gets and sets the object associated with the <xref href="System.UriTemplateMatch"></xref> instance.
When you add a <xref:System.UriTemplate> to a <xref:System.UriTemplateTable> you associate data with the template.
This value is application specific; no particular semantics are associated with this value.

When <xref:System.UriTemplateTable.Match%28System.Uri%29> is called and a match is found the data associated with the matching template is returned in the <xref:System.UriTemplateMatch.Data%2A> property.
An <xref href="System.Object"></xref> instance.
Gets a collection of query string parameters and their values.
All query string name/value pairs from the original URI appear in this collection, even if they are not explicitly specified in the template string that was matched.
The values in this collection have been had all escape sequences translated into actual characters.
A <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.NameValueCollection"></xref> instance that contains the query string parameters and their values.
Gets a collection of relative path segments.
This property contains a collection of the path segments from the candidate URI that matched the template along with path segments that matched a template wildcard.
Path segments that matched a template wildcard are also contained in the <xref:System.UriTemplateMatch.WildcardPathSegments%2A> property.
A collection of relative path segments.
Gets and sets the matched URI.
A <xref href="System.Uri"></xref> instance.
Gets and sets the <xref href="System.UriTemplate"></xref> instance associated with this <xref href="System.UriTemplateMatch"></xref> instance.
This property contains the <xref:System.UriTemplate> that the candidate URI matched.
A <xref href="System.UriTemplate"></xref> instance.
Gets a collection of path segments that are matched by a wildcard in the URI template.
A collection of path segments that are matched by a wildcard in the URI template.
